  "prompt": "What's the meaning of ISO?",
  "response": "ISO can have several meanings depending on the context:\n\n1. **International Organization for Standardization**: ISO is a non-governmental international organization that develops and publishes standards to ensure quality, safety, efficiency, and interoperability of products, services, and systems across various industries.\n\n2. **Image Stabilization Option**: In photography, ISO refers to the sensitivity of a camera's sensor to light. A higher ISO setting allows for better performance in low light but can introduce more noise into the image.\n\n3. **ISO File**: In computing, an ISO file is a disk image of an optical disc, which contains all the data from the disc in a single file. It is often used for software distribution, backups, and creating virtual drives.\n\n4. **Isometric**: In mathematics and video game design, ISO might refer to isometric projection, which is a method for visually representing three-dimensional objects in two dimensions.\n\nMake sure to consider the context in which the term is used to determine the appropriate meaning.",
